Four years ago, 10,000 Czech citizens voted for MPs abroad.
"Since the last amendment of the Order in 2013, there have been some changes that need to be taken into account in these lists," the Ministry explains.
"New representative offices have been created in some countries, some offices have been closed, or the level of representation has changed," the material reads.
The decree contains two annexes, the first of which lists the representative offices to which paper ballots are supplied.
