Riodoce employees miss Valdez. the man was known for his wit and indiscriminate language. he was a good friend who liked to give advice and hugs -- a teacher who knew how to survive.
They all relied on his daily routine.
He always wore his cap.
He often went to the El Guayabo bar across from the offices and sat at the same table.
Now they ask: did this routine cause his death?
His death also raised questions about their own assumptions - how do you do your job best and stay alive?
"They don't like you messing with their wives, children, clean shops, secret landing sites."
